00:11:18,081 --> 00:11:21,022
Or I can record Jack, who sounds like a pig, for example,

225
00:11:21,022 --> 00:11:23,063
which can be very useful.

226
00:11:23,063 --> 00:11:26,685
Then animals, I would, you know, look into pigs, horses,

227
00:11:26,685 --> 00:11:28,485
donkeys, elephant, walrus, all that stuff,

228
00:11:28,485 --> 00:11:30,866
which, you know, kind of has some kind of quality

229
00:11:30,866 --> 00:11:33,067
I would look for in a dragon in this case.

230
00:11:33,067 --> 00:11:34,428
And then also the non-literal stuff,

231
00:11:34,428 --> 00:11:37,809
like dry, some metal, cellophane, door creaks.

