00:50:19,690 --> 00:50:23,492
So I'm curious about your process for making variations.

910
00:50:23,492 --> 00:50:25,674
So once you have the first variation,

911
00:50:25,674 --> 00:50:28,815
do you tend to be able to just rely on modulating

912
00:50:28,815 --> 00:50:30,536
those existing source assets?

913
00:50:30,536 --> 00:50:32,597
Or do you have to bring in totally different assets

914
00:50:32,597 --> 00:50:33,598
for the other variations?

915
00:50:33,772 --> 00:50:40,054
Yeah, so that's actually a very good question and I can't believe I haven't covered that in my presentation, but it's a very good...

916
00:50:40,054 --> 00:50:46,057
So again, when I was talking about the source, obviously, you know, what you normally do is you create...

917
00:50:46,057 --> 00:50:51,880
So if I record myself screaming, for example, I would create several different variations of that.

918
00:50:52,200 --> 00:50:57,586
in the first place. So then later on, and also all like modern libraries do that as well,

919
00:50:57,586 --> 00:51:01,330
they provide one sound but they also provide you know eight different variations or six variations.

920
00:51:01,330 --> 00:51:07,618
And then what I would do is as long as I get one sound to work in my in my session like an

921
00:51:07,978 --> 00:51:12,382
an attack sound for example, I would then duplicate the whole thing and try and shift

922
00:51:12,382 --> 00:51:18,248
everything so I use the next kind of variation of that. See if it works and then the whole

923
00:51:18,248 --> 00:51:23,133
game starts again. It probably doesn't work so again I would replace layers but again

924
00:51:23,133 --> 00:51:26,115
obviously because I already set some kind of style with the first variation.

925
00:51:26,716 --> 00:51:28,077
then it gets more complicated.

926
00:51:28,077 --> 00:51:30,079
But yeah, I would tend to do,

927
00:51:30,079 --> 00:51:32,322
sorry, I would tend to duplicate the sounds

928
00:51:32,322 --> 00:51:35,445
and try and just to change the files itself.

929
00:51:35,445 --> 00:51:35,645
Okay.

930
00:51:35,645 --> 00:51:37,347
And then see again if it works,

931
00:51:37,347 --> 00:51:38,769
and if it doesn't work, then I have to restart.

932
00:51:38,769 --> 00:51:39,650
So is it actually the opposite?

933
00:51:39,650 --> 00:51:42,873
You leave the modulation and pitching more or less the same

934
00:51:42,873 --> 00:51:43,093
and then.

935
00:51:43,313 --> 00:51:45,694
Yeah, no, I mean, obviously, you know, the pitching can vary.

936
00:51:45,694 --> 00:51:48,455
So that's in, um, oh yeah, I see what you mean.

937
00:51:48,455 --> 00:51:52,696
No, yeah, I would leave it the same because you know, most of these sounds

938
00:51:52,696 --> 00:51:56,118
would then work, but then if I play the second sound, if I play the second

939
00:51:56,118 --> 00:51:59,979
variation, the pitch is again, shifting slightly, I then go back into the

940
00:51:59,979 --> 00:52:01,839
different layers and try to match them together again.

941
00:52:01,839 --> 00:52:05,040
And then for the third and fourth and fifth variation, it's exactly the same.

942
00:52:05,040 --> 00:52:05,601
Awesome.

